JS / Programming Terms
======================

variable
  A named box that holds a value.
  const name = "bailey"

const
  A variable that cannot be reassigned.
  const name = "bailey"

let
  A variable that CAN be reassigned.
  let name = "bailey"
  name = "bubba"  // fine

function
  A reusable block of code. Run it by calling it with ().
  function greet() { print("hey") }
  greet()

method
  A function that belongs to an object. Called with a dot.
  now.getDay()   // getDay is a method on the Date object

property
  A value that belongs to an object. No () needed.
  array.length

class
  A blueprint for creating objects.
  Date is a class — new Date() creates one from that blueprint.

argument
  The value you pass into a function when calling it.
  createPoll("", 1000, fn)  // "", 1000, fn are arguments

parameter
  The name for an argument inside the function definition.
  function greet(name) {}   // name is the parameter

return
  What a function gives back as its result.
  function double(n) { return n * 2 }
  double(4)  // gives back 8

export default
  Exports the main thing from a file. Imported without {}.
  import Clock from "./Clock"

named export
  Exports multiple things from a file. Imported with {}.
  import { Clock, Something } from "./Clock"
